      "widgets_values": [
        "BLUNT -> Repose -> Flux Fill\n\n1. Load your photo  2. BLUNT generates a Gaussian splat locally  3. Repose the camera in GaussianViewer Lift and click 'Set Camera'  4. Queue prompt -> Flux Fill repairs only the masked artifact regions, which should preserve the chosen camera better than full-frame editing."
      ],
      "_meta": {
        "title": "Workflow Guide"
      },
      "color": "#233",
      "bgcolor": "#355"
    },
